headline: LKQ Stock Is S&P 500’s Worst Performer. Fewer Cars Are Being Repaired.
summary: Shares of  LKQ  were plummeting Thursday after the automotive parts and services company reported a smaller-than-expected quarterly profit and lowered its financial forecasts for the full year.  The company posted adjusted earnings of 87 cents a share, below analysts’ consensus estimate of 92 cents and down 11% from the prior year.  LKQ  stock was down 21% on Thursday, putting it on track for its largest percentage decrease on record and its lowest close since Oct. 28, 2020.

headline: LKQ cuts 2025 earnings outlook on soft demand for auto parts
summary: Tariff-related uncertainty and higher insurance costs have pressured LKQ’s margins and reduced the number of repairable insurance claims.  LKQ now expects adjusted earnings per share between $3.00 and $3.30 for 2025, down from its previous outlook of $3.40 to $3.70.  LKQ, which also sells scrap and other materials to metal recyclers, second-quarter revenue fell 1.9% to $3.64 billion, from a year earlier.

headline: LKQ’s (NASDAQ:LKQ) Q2 Earnings Results: Revenue In Line With Expectations But Stock Drops
